tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 20, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104xpq1665702796932.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xpq1665702796932.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xpq1665702796932.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"xpq1665702796932\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                     \n Global ProcScript Library Editor\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"xpq1665702796932__global_procscript_library_editor_22618\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Use the Global ProcScript Library Editor to create and edit Global ProcScript modules, which are linked into components at runtime when called from ProcScript in a Uniface application.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xpq1665702796932__p_d5624e1_d5625e1_d5626e1\">A new or updated Global ProcScript must be compiled to generate the runtime object. If Uniface detects errors in the code, you must correct the error or comment out the incorrect code.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xpq1665702796932__topic_d3277e1_d3278e1_d3279e1_d3280e1_d3281e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d712889e60\">\n                       \n Worksheets\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xpq1665702796932__li_d2741e1_d2742e1_d2743e1\">Define Structure—create new Global ProcScript objects and edit their properties.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xpq1665702796932__li_d2744e1_d2745e1_d2746e1\">Write Script—write the code for the Global ProcScript.\n </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xpq1665702796932__topic_d3282e1_d3283e1_d3284e1_d3285e1_d3286e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d712889e75\">\n                       \n How to\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xpq1665702796932__p_d5633e1_d5634e1_d5635e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jfg1705567612144.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jfg1705567612144.html\" title=\"Global ProcScript modules are defined and deployed in Global ProcScript libraries.\">Creating Global ProcScripts</a>\n</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xpq1665702796932__li_d2747e1_d2748e1_d2749e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qle1665702773192.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qle1665702773192.html\" title=\"Use the Uniface IDE to develop an application, following the Uniface development paradigm of Model, Construct, Build, and Deploy.\">Using the Uniface IDE</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xpq1665702796932__li_d2750e1_d2751e1_d2752e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dkp1665702773261.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dkp1665702773261.html\" title=\"Although development objects can be quite different in content and purpose, the way you create, edit and delete them in the Uniface IDE is essentially the same.\">Working with Development Objects</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cvq1665702579531.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Global ProcScripts</a><p>Global ProcScripts are global objects that are located in a runtime library and can be called from any ProcScript in the application. They enable you to define common functionality for use by one or more applications.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bka1665702579213.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>call</a><p>Execute the specified function or global ProcScript.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533843\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533843\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Global ProcScript Library Editor Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 20, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Global ProcScript Library Editor Use the Global ProcScript Library Editor to create and edit Global ProcScript modules, which are linked into components at runtime when called from ProcScript in a Uniface application. A new or updated Global ProcScript must be compiled to generate the runtime object. If Uniface detects errors in the code, you must correct the error or comment out the incorrect code. Worksheets Define Structure—create new Global ProcScript objects and edit their properties. Write Script—write the code for the Global ProcScript. How to Creating Global ProcScripts Using the Uniface IDE Working with Development Objects Related Links Global ProcScripts Global ProcScripts are global objects that are located in a runtime library and can be called from any ProcScript in the application. They enable you to define common functionality for use by one or more applications. call Execute the specified function or global ProcScript. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}